### Hadith 2:567

*Narrated 'Umar:*

Once I gave a horse in Allah's Cause (in charity) but that person did
not take care of it. I intended to buy it, as I thought he would sell it
at a low price. So, I asked the Prophet (p.b.u.h) about it. He said,
"Neither buy, nor take back your alms which you have given, even if the
seller were willing to sell it for one Dirham, for he who takes back his
alms is like the one who swallows his own vomit."

